Ah, good call! You can get that with if let if you’re sure about one variant. But here’s the fix — since your enum only has one variant, it’s safer (and idiomatic) to use `if let` instead of `match`. That way, you avoid a situation where someone adds another variant in the future and forgets to cover all arms in match. Here’s how you’d do it with if let:

```rust
if let MyEnum::MyVariant(x) = my_enum {
    // handle x
}
